%section
  %h1 Animations
%section
  %pre
    %code
      :preserve
        @keyframes myAnimation{
          from{
            width: 10px;
          }
          to{
            width: 100px;
          }
        }
  %p.note
    Animations are declared as <code>@keyframes</code> (with a name). This is where
    the states of the animation are defined. In its simplest form, we can set a
    start (<code>from</code>) and an end (<code>to</code>).
%section
  %pre
    %code
      :preserve
        @keyframes myAnimation{
          0%{
            width: 10px;
          }
          50%{
            width: 80px;
          }
          100%{
            width: 100px;
          }
        }
  %p.note
    For animations with more than two steps, we can use percentages to
    define each <i>keyframe</i>.
%section
