  %p.note
    The animation keyframes are assigned to an elment with the <code>animation</code>
    property. We can also set the duration of the animation (in <code>s</code>
    or <code>ms</code>), and the number of repetitions (it can be <code>infinite</code>).
%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="vYBZzYP" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    We can also use the <code>alternate</code> keyword if we want the animation to reverse once it has completed a repetition.


%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="bGbRxEE" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    With <code>animation-fill-mode: forwards</code> an element will remain in
    its last keyframe once the animation has ended.
  %p.note
    With <code>animation-play-state: paused</code> an animation can be paused
    at a specific time (i.e. on :hover).

